  <refnamediv>
    <refname>lowdisc_corrcoef</refname>
    <refpurpose>Correlation coefficients</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   r = lowdisc_corrcoef ( x )
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>x :</term>
      <listitem><para> a m-by-n matrix of doubles, the data. <literal>m</literal> is the number of observations. <literal>n</literal> is the number of variables.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>r :</term>
      <listitem><para> a n-by-n matrix of doubles, the correlation coefficient.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
Returns the matrix <literal>r</literal> of correlation coefficients calculated from an
input matrix <literal>x</literal>.
The matrix <literal>r</literal> is related to the covariance matrix <literal>c=cov(x)</literal> by
   </para>
   <para>
<literal>r(i,j) = c(i,j) / sqrt(c(i,i) * c(j,j)).</literal>
   </para>
   <para>
The cov function comes from Stixbox.
   </para>
   <para>
TODO : return p-values
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
// Uncorrelated data
x = grand(30,4,"nor",0,1)
// Introduce correlation.
x(:,4) = sum(x,2);
// Compute sample correlation
r = lowdisc_corrcoef ( x )

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

